# Puzzle content lives in a separate private repo now, not this public one --
# committing them here used to mean anyone browsing GitHub could read
# future-dated (unplayed) puzzles' full board state and solution days before
# they went live (reproduced live: 2026-07-20 through 2026-07-23 were
# already exposed here while only up to 2026-07-19 had actually rotated in).
# Local dev still just drops puzzle .py files straight into this same
# backend/puzzles/ directory -- they're only untracked *from git*, nothing
# about how puzzle_registry.py discovers/loads them changes.
backend/puzzles/*.py
